snippet.textDisplay:
As a woman who lost her jobs to neurological disability, is unable to claim ESA because of the 2 year NI contribution rule, lives in a structurally dangerous run down park home caravan that I have no money to fix, made to sign a letter by the council to say that if anything happens to myself/others under my roof due to the unsafe conditions it is my responsibility, as I 'declined' to take the council's advice ( said advice being that I would need to find between 4 to 6 thousand pounds to pay half the repair estimate ), not offered any alternative accommodation, not been reviewed by consultant for progressive disability for over 2 years, zero symptom support from GP , I am losing hope. As I sit here, huddled around a free standing radiator, feeling the wind blowing through the holes in the mouldy walls, rotted window frames and gaps in the boards laid over the crumbling floors that have fallen through, I have to wonder if I should let the next infection I get just take it's natural course.
This has been my experience of austerity under the Conservative government. This is the reality of becoming disabled at working age - we are no longer valued as human beings.
